items.text: Chicken rice: Locals tell us Tong Fong Fatt #01-49 is d best of all their branches in SG. After ordering a few plates, we agree! Definitely better value than Loy Kee @ Balestier!
Nasi lemak: 01-07. Join d long queue. Isn't it obvious? ;-)
chwee kueh
Johnson duck here's pretty awesome
Ghim Moh Nasi Lemak still good after all these years :)
Prata: There's only 1 place 2 get ur prata in the morning: Mohd Faisal #01-61. That's all they make! Luv their thick curry.
Chai tow kway. Unlike Lian He #01-30 which binds dish with a layer of omelette, Hock Soon #01-18 is more traditional style: chunky, slightly burnt, lots of chai por (chopped fermented radish). Nice!
Try Feng Sheng Hainanese Chicken Rice from Dover awesome damn nice ♥☺
The renovated popular food centre has re-opened at its original place with change of management. Some food items prices have increased, stallholder commented its due to higher rental.
Mohd Faisal Roti Prata. Good with the Fish Curry.
Tong Fong Fatt Hainanese Boneless Chicken Rice is good
九江燒臘's roasted duck is really delicious. No wonder there is always a long queue.
Old time resident tip #1: try chuan kee boneless braised duck rice facing blk 19. Long queues at times but worth the wait! Extra tip - try weekends. The young chap inside is more experienced!
Lots of good food here. Just follow the long queue!
The mui fun & hor fun stall only operates from 5-830pm in the evenings. Come any later& you'll miss it!
Jiu jiang shao la cha siu  roast pork roast duck  is one of the best in sg. Must try: Hock soon carrot cake, tong fong fatt hainanese chicken rice, guan kee char kuay teow, jwee kuay
Bring lots of tissue paper to clean up the table or chairs which tend to be quite dirty amidst the breakfast or lunchtime crowds
The renovated market & food centre has re-opened at its original place on 1 Mar 2016. Some of the food items have increased price by S$0.50 O.o
Yong tau foo great. A china looking aunty....
Bf here !!
Sanmo western food is nice #01-73
Keng kee dim sum is AWESOME! Awesome char Siew paos and awesome service.
Generous mug of quality ABC fruit juice for only S$2.50 at Fruitz n Juz Xpress @ #01-28 👍 [ABC = Apple +Beetroot +Carrot =Miracle Drink  Cooling nutritious drink on a hot afternoon to quench thirst.
The existing market is under renovation. Has moved to a temporary location along the Ghim Moh road.
Wanton noodles at #01-43 is fairly cheap at $3. Fine springy noodles & good meaty wanton.
Car park charge $1.28 for first hour even if you park for less than half hour.
The char kuay teow is overrated,  doesnt taste as good as it used to. Chwee kuay makes a great pre meal starter
Must try the dim sum at keng kee tim sum stall! Char siew bao yi zi bang! (Y)
Keng Kee dimsum power! Chat Siew Bao die die must try!!!
Love 烧鸭烧肉饭..
The mui fan and hor fun is super!
Finish a meal with Ah Balling's peanut soup. Yummy!
You can find Ah Seng Durian here! Remember to book your spiky friends in advance before you head down!
Masala thosai: We make a pilgrimage to Heavens Indian Curry #01-15 whenever we get thosai or apom cravings. Their curries r savory (makes me salivate typing dis)
Like I said Hor FuN stall is the best and healthy...... Not oily and tasty......
Chai tau kuey (fried carrot cake): My 1st bite brought me back 2 my childhood. D wok-fried fragrance fr stall #01-30 was so addictive dat my kids hijacked my dish! Generous amt of chai por too!
Hiananese Boneless Chicken Rice is simply the best. (Y)
Yummy stuff: Chwee kueh, chee cheong fun, pontian wontan noodles n dim sum
guan kee char kway teow, char siew rice from jiu jiang shao la, ghim moh chwee kueh, tadpole burbur chacha from golden swallow desserts - they are some of the best in their own leagues!
Best Tosai can be found here. Must trys: princess apam, royal Tosai, butter onion Tosai.
Ice kacang is the best here. Come down here to try it :))
Try the balonglong fruit juice, it's deliciously tarty. Sold at the fruit stall facing the shops (shop and save side)
The beef hor fun is a must-try here. Be prepared to queue though.
Saw people order semi-cut open durian from popular Ah Seng Durian stall at wet market and carry a small basket (as tray) with durians and dine at hawker centre as fruit / dessert after proper meal.
Should try the roti prata here  in the morning sooo delicous

Beef hor fun from Hin Fried Beef Hor Fun 01-56. The "wok hei" (smokiness from stir frying) comes from the masterful tossing by the chef. If beef is not your thing, they also offer prawns & sliced fish
Give lor mee a miss
I ONLY EAT THE CHWEE KUEH HERE!! The lard-infused chai por cooked over the charcoal flame 😍😍😍😍
I strongly recommend you to try these foods: 1)ghim moh chwee kueh 2)88 chicken rice 5) Ghim Moh Chee Cheong Fun 6) Granny's pancake 7) Tai Chong Coffee Stall. 8) Ah Balling Peanut Soup.
Ghim moh food centre is 1 of the bet place to find tasty food
Teck Hin Beef House is the original one. Not the stall they used to be at.
Guan kee kway teow is pretty good, but not good worth the 50 mins wait. Chee kway is way OVERRATED! greasy n owner is stingy w the topping,but I m glad they din give more cos it taste kinda gross....
Dont buy from ang's chicken rice. Owner fucking niao!! Guailan fucker!
Jiu jiang shao la is the best roast duck in Singapore. Really! A bit salty but full of flavour because they have a real charcoal roaster.
I like the soup here.
Chwee kueh at #01-54 is cheap & quite solid packed. But chai por was salty.

Ghim Moh Chwee Kueh 李老三水粿 at #01-54, 6pcs for S$2.10 at the renovated food centre. Still one of the most appetizing Chwee Kueh fragrant and texture that I've eaten, eventhough Cai Poh feels more salty
Plssssssss don't try that cha kway teow Stall, no doubt long queue..... it's sooooooooo oily lahhhhh...... That old man also yaya payaya..... Hehehehe....
Fried kway teow is nice!!
Be prepare to Q at lease 10mins ..and the  shui kui stall not as nice as before .. well almost everything every stall have Q!
The black carrot cake is really good!!
Chwee kueh is not as good as how the others recommended. Owner is stingy in giving the 菜圃！
Keng kee dim sum is thes best! Must try their char siew bao. Die die must try!
Soup at 01-63 ...the chicken leg soup taste of expire oil smell
Try hock soon carrot cake.die die must try.
Soya milk: There r several stalls but d 1 dat ultimately tastes freshly made is #01-01
Big brother of RuJi Fishball Noodles (at Holland Drive market & Old Airport Rd) Good stuff!!
Jiu jiang shao la has a really long queue and isn't that fantastic. The one behind the Guan Kee Fried Kway Teow is much nicer. The Heong Hut fishball noodle isn't nice when it opens during cny.
Very difficult to find places during lunch time. If u manage to get one, the table is very dirty.
#01-34 Vegetarian food.
Come early b4 lunch hours.. Full hse here...
Very near to buy eveth;
Heavens Indian Curry has great food.
As for me I only like the Hor FuN Stall, Nice and faster queue..... The rest not up to my standard.... Hehehehe....
Tong Fong Fatt hainanese boneless chicken rice, absolute best in town
#01-14 Hakka Yong Tau Foo! Must try!
Ample vacant carpark lot surround this food centre during evening time for casual dinner, as lesser food stalls are open in evening.
The black carrot cake at #01-16 Ghim Moh Carrot Cake is nice.
Fishball noodle: Heong Huat 01-50 was surprisingly delicious! Luv d bouncy fishballs
#01-49 Tong Fatt Hainanese Boneless chicken rice
Thosai at #01-15 is fantastic! Try the Royal Thosai for $3.50
Chicken rice and duck rice awesome
Delicious, fragrant & smooth Fried Hor Fun with 'wok hei' topped with thick slices of fresh fish meat. Value-for-money delicious food from Hin Fried Hor Fun With Prawn, Beef and Sliced Fish stall.
Great food at very good prices! Not for the fussy!
Straits Times recommended Miso Carbonara with Onsen egg looks very appealing ;-)
Try the chicken briyani, masala thosai or cheese masala thosai.
Prata is nice! But only available in the morning.
汤圆
Try the chwee kueh!
Teck hin fried hor fun, beef house. Can't go wrong with these hor fun! Fish and beef are good! Try them!
Fave: juice, roti prata, bakteh soup,
Jin hua seafood new join n sliced fish soup....can do lah....
After 48hrs of fluid meals post-tooth surgery, I finally can naturally bite soft vegetables and slices of fish meat from this delicious bowl of Bittergourd Fish Soup-style Porridge when its chilled.
Roast duck by Jiu Jiang Shao La, Mui fan n hor fun right next door, another super long q at char kway teow stall n excellent dessert options. Why don't I come here more often?
Must eat the beef steak fried rice!! Really good!
The chao guo tiao here is really good. To find it, just find the longest que.
Carrot cake, chwee kway, prata, char kway tiao, chicken rice, duck rice... All worth trying! Yum!
Nice beef and sliced fish hor fun!!
There are "two" teck hin hor funs now. The one between the coffee stall and the fishball noodle stall is the original chef! Try it to tell the difference!!!
Currently in a makeshift area till renovations are done for this market. Ghim moh chwee kueh is ultra old school here.
Ah balling peanut soup is good. #01-43
Mi chiam kueh (local pancake): Granny's Pancake #01-24 offers 4 fillings: peanut, coconut, red bean & peanut butter! D long q is due 2 meticulous preparation: cook batter, slice, pack, clean. Whew!
Kway chap rocks!
Possibly the best chwee kueh in Singapore here. Am also a regular at the nasi lemak store, which sells great breakfast bee hoon.
Tasty fresh fruit juice at only $2! Doesn't get any better than this. Avocado milkshake's highly recommended!

Popular secret recipe stock cooked hor fun with wok-hei from Hin Fried Hor Fun With Prawn, Beef And Sliced Fish is now at #01-56 at the newly re-opened Ghim Moh Food Centre. Price increased by S$0.50.
Not much places where u can find cold dessert for less than 2 dollars! Go golden swallow dessert! 01-53!
A must to buy da bao from keng kee dim sum! Awesome!!
Unless u r willing to queue, else there is no way you can ever taste the hugely popular char Kway teow. Duck rice, heaven's Indian curry dosai, hor fun are other good options.
They have the best carrot cake ever.
Must try their G Pisang... Very nice
Jap jae fan...cheap and good
GUAN KEE FRIED KUAY TEOW
Lee Wee Bros Nasi Lemak quite gd and halal.
Hock Hin black carrot cake is awesome. Yummy.
best Hainanese Chicken Rice here!!
2 thumbs up for a new kid on the block. Fishball noodles from Tom's City Zoom #01-11. Generous portions of fishballs, fish cakes, & vegetables. Handmade fishballs are odd-shaped but chewy
Super braised duck!! I think it's called Chuan Kee Duck... Will confirm.
Best chicken rice Tong Fong Fatt
Absolutely love the mee hoon kuay and tee kah chor from 101 home made noodle shop!! One of the best, asides from my mum's cooking!! Am always coming back for it although am no longer living nearby!
Enjoy e food here whilr u can theyll be shifting e market in a year or two
#01-55 Thye Hong Fish Ball Noodle 太丰鱼圆面
#Pasta & #donburi by Kenny, #01-53: #miso #carbonara #onsen #egg pasta $7; #panfried #salmon #veggie pasta $7.5; salmon donburi $7.5
Damn lok kok... Oldies area.... One of the few really old hawker centre around in SG
Traditional Cantonese Fish Porridge plus Egg (minus You Tiao) for lunch again at Temporary Stall #01-40. One of my favourite liquid meal during the first few days after tooth surgery.
Chuan Kee Braised Duck Kway Teow and porridge!! Love <3
Prata is nice but on some days is fantastic....only cannot tahan the queue....
Get yr drinks from Tat Seng Coffee Stall. The lady boss here provides restaurant level service: she even said "thanks for patronising" in Mandarin and the drinks are cheap too! ^.^
Keng kee dim sum damn power syiok ah love the Luo mai gai  :D
Nice beef hor fun

Saw lady using 'Christian Care' c/o ..Marketing And Wholesale Singapore to seek S$10 charitable exchange for S$10 spa voucher. Office lunch crowd still donating. Such Scam was alerted on 'Crime Watch'
Ngee Heng Kuay Chap, the Kuay is hard and soup no taste.
Try out the fresh made soya milk here (#01-03)!
Roast meat and Char Siew from Jiu Jiang Shao la is yummy!
The Chendol is superb!
Chwee kueh (steamed rice cakes): If u r a fan of Tiong Bahru's, u will find d famous #01-31 a tad too soft & soggy. And very little toppings (& salty!)
Fried Kway Teow is nothin to shout about. Quite generous with ingredients tho.
Must try the Kang Shang Hua wanton noodle.. Nice!
88 chicken rice is new and deliciousss!
Always fresh veggie n fruits! Market opens at 3plus-4am
Teck Hin fried horfun stall's serving is huge! Good for big eaters! always got long queue too
good curry fish head here; it used to be at Dover Market
Do try the chwee kueh here! Fresh and nice!
Ghim moh nasi lemak... One of the best that I haf tried!! Thumb up!!!
the apom and the ice kacang is good
Love the Ghim Moh chwee kueh, fried carrot cake, jiu jiang roast duck etc.
spinach dumpling noodle for a tasty light treat. I was looking for a light brunch just before going for a workout. This tasty noodle satusfied my craving. I dont feel bloated.
Keng kee dim sum aunty the best, very good service and excellent food. Must try the siew mai and char siew bao!
Soon lee hor fun is awesome!!!! Esp de beef!!!!!
So much good food. ... yummmmy. Slurp!  Char Siew duck carrot cake woooo!!
Super cheap sugar cane @sin ma sugar cane juice! $1 only!
Love the Chwee Kweh here!  Was talking to the stall owners and they hv been selling here for over 30 years.  But their experience is over 50 years!
try braised duck rice. Char kuay tiaw is over rated.
Best chwee kueh in singapore! Must try!
Must try lucky Poh hong kong noodle and rice .... The dumplings and chicken are damn nice!
Ah Bo Ling (glutinous rice ball dessert):  #01-43 serves w peanut soup. Family voted dat Maxwell Rd Mkt was more delicious & fragrant. Still makes gr8 snack when u dun want any of savoury fare here
Chwee kueh here is the most expensive in Singapore at $1.40 for 4. The stall is also very stingy with their chye poh.
Wantan Mee. Sea City #01-43 serves a yummy bowl of WTM. Noodles are springy 'q'. Wantans are generous sizes.
Nice vegetarian bee hoon
so sian!!! ;(
九江烧腊, they gave a generous amount of meat with only $5! Would prefer the gravy to be Saltish instead of sweet.
The dessert stall here is da bomb!
Not sure when Heck Hin Fried Hor Fun moved. But they are no longer at the original unit. They are right opposite at 01-51. Don't go to the wrong one.
Market is currently closed for renovation until early Mar 2016
Mince meat noodle, Prawn noodle and chee cheong fun is must try
